{"TEG":[{"def":"A sheep in its second year; also, a doe in its second year.","pos":""}],"TEGMEN":[{"def":"The inner layer of the coating of a seed, usually thin and delicate; the endopleura.","pos":""},{"def":"One of the elytra of an insect, especially of certain Orthoptera.","pos":""}],"TEGMENTAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a tegument or tegmentum; as, the tegmental layer of the epiblast; the tegmental cells of the taste buds.","pos":""}],"TEGMENTUM":[{"def":"A covering; -- applied especially to the bundles of longitudinal fibers in the upper part of the crura of the cerebrum.","pos":""}],"TEGUEXIN":[{"def":"A large South American lizard (Tejus teguexin).","pos":""}],"TEGULA":[{"def":"A small appendage situated above the base of the wings of Hymenoptera and attached to the mesonotum.","pos":""}],"TEGULAR":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a tile; resembling a tile, or arranged like tiles; consisting of tiles; as, a tegular pavement.","pos":""}],"TEGULATED":[{"def":"Composed of small plates, as of horn or metal, overlapping like tiles; -- said of a kind of ancient armor.","pos":""}],"TEGUMENT":[{"def":"A cover or covering; an integument.","pos":""},{"def":"Especially, the covering of a living body, or of some part or organ of such a body; skin; hide.","pos":""}],"TEGUMENTARY":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a tegument or teguments; consisting of teguments; serving as a tegument or covering.","pos":""}]}